history.content: The reason you're not enrolled in the course despite the number of open seats in the lecture is because there are not enough lab seats available.  The trick to getting into the course is having a seat in all three sections.  In order for us to open up another lab, the we'll have to have approval to higher another GSI.  In the meantime, your best bet is to find an available seat in the lab and discussions section in addition to the lecture.  The system selects those students from the wait list first.
